f=Engineering/quinn/custom/regression-map/SKILL.md · in=regression-map department's memory system fragile: curated, append-only registry areas broken before (or cypher/aegis proved breakable), guarded named targeted-regression suite. Any diff touching mapped area run area's suite quinn's gate. self-annealing mechanism incident, red-team finding, recurring flake makes map (and therefore gate) smarter. · p=Systems don't break uniformly; they break they've always broken timezone handling, payment retry, auth edge case. Teams re-learn hard way because knowledge lives nobody's head after quarter. map writes down wires gate, third regression spot caught procedure, luck. · wu=Triggers: "regression map," "fragile areas," "has broken before," "add map entry," post-incident (ops's post-mortem output), cypher/aegis finding closed, flaky test recurring, automatically gate check (test-strategy consults it). · st:/ Protocol=`FEED (what creates/updates entries — self-annealing inputs) \· ops post-mortem → entry (what broke, why, the guard test) \· cypher finding closed → entry (the attack path, the guard) \· aegis vuln fixed → entry (the vuln class + surface) \· bug fix merged → entry (per gate-matrix: the fix's failing-test-first becomes the guard)` · in=**Every incident feeds map.** ops post-mortem doesn't produce map entry (or explicitly justify none needed) incomplete self-annealing loop's load-bearing step. **Entries specific testable.** template: area (paths/modules/flows), it's fragile (incident/finding refs real events, vibes), guard (named test suite exercises failure mode), history (dates broke). entry without runnable guard TODO, flagged. **The gate consults map.** Touched-area matching runs gate check; match makes entry's suite mandatory (matrix tier R). guard suite exists gate FAILS map entry's TODO fragility without guard blocks, doesn't warn. **Flaky register.** Recurring flaky tests live here: test, suspected cause, owner, quarantine date. Quarantined tests count coverage holes (test-strategy's rule) until fixed their subject guarded another way. **Retire architecture, optimism.** "It hasn't broken while" never retires entry. structural removal fragility cited ADR retires one, retired entries stay file history. **No invented fragility.** Entries trace real events (incidents, findings, fix history). Speculative "this looks scary" areas listed separate watchlist section, labeled reasoning-based rule 0.6, don't gate. · of=`## Map Check: [diff/change] \· Areas touched: [none / entry ids] \· Required targeted suites: [list] — present+green: [✓/✗] \· Flaky-register impact: [none / holes] \· → feeds test-strategy gate verdict (tier R)` · pr=**Fragility fact citation** entries trace real breaks, findings, fixes; speculation labeled watchlist, doesn't gate., **No guard, pass** mapped area without runnable guard blocks gate; unguarded known fragility worst kind., **Append-only, retire-by-ADR** history value; optimism retires nothing., **Every post-mortem feeds map says not** annealing loop silent exits., **The map makes gate smarter, bigger** targeted suites touched areas, blanket full-suite runs. · f=Empty map (new business) normal; fills first incident/finding. State gate tier inactive until entries exist., Guard suite slow per-change runs split: fast targeted core (gates) full suite (scheduled); split recorded entry., Disagreement over whether area "touched" err toward running suite; repeated false-positive matching refines entry's path/flow definition (logged entry correction, reference). · b:with Other Skills=**test-strategy** (sibling) owns gate; map supplies tier R's requirements flaky register floors count., **ops** (incident-response) authors post-mortems; skill turns them guarded entries handoff mandatory directions., **charter-enforcement** (sibling) routes closed cypher/aegis findings entries finding isn't closed until it's mapped., **dev/architecture-decisions**: retirement requires ADR removed fragility; map cites it.